wikipedia_page.main: Archibald Williamson, 1st Baron Forres PC (13 September 1860 – 29 October 1931), known as Sir Archibald Williamson, 1st Baronet, from 1909 to 1922, was a British businessman and Liberal politician.

response: *Archibald Williamson, 1st Baron Forres, 1st Baronet of Glenlogil (1860–1931)

The Moray and Nairn by-election, 1922 was a parliamentary by-election held for the British House of Commons constituency of Moray and Nairn on 21 June 1922.  The seat had become vacant when the Coalition Liberal Member of Parliament (MP) Archibald Williamson, 1st Baron Forres was elevated to the peerage as Baron Forres.  He had held the seat since its creation at the 1918 general election.
